The findings are real in the cited code: integer serialization slices bytes, request commitment is trie-based, RLP header presence checks are incomplete, transaction data is inserted raw, TxPool ignores max fee caps, and `ClRequest` does not validate byte-sized types. I’m checking constructor and raw serialization details next so the edits don’t change the public shape more than needed.
